Scientists at the University of California, Berkley, show that if Walmart increased the average wage to $12 an hour, it would cost the group $3.2 billion.
That’s 1.1% more than what it currently spends.
If Walmart shifted the entire increase in wages to consumers’ shoulders, each race in the store would cost them an additional 46 cents.
They will spend only $12.39 more in a year than they do now.
Walmart supporters note with satisfaction that the protests took place in only nine states and did no harm to the group.
The "Black Friday" continued in stores from 8am to midnight the next day and Walmart sold over that period 5000 items per second.
His coffers made a total of 100 million transactions for "Black Friday".
