He can declare, "We're going to change the law and allow it," but he can't say that we're going to act as if nothing was.
The law on contracts contains relatively strict rules on the formalities to be completed, precisely to protect the call for tenders.
But it is also tragic that a bidder is eliminated solely because of formal defects.
The law will never be perfect, but its application must be just and that is, in my opinion, what is lacking in our country.
