To reach the city, you can take one of the new highways of M Pena Nieto, a significant improvement has been made to these roads, once bumpy and full of crevices.
Plaques bearing his name are hung outside a new sports complex and an impressive interactive museum dedicated to climate change.
“We count on him to bring about lasting change,” said his friend and political ally Gabriel Olvera Hernandez, a member of Congress and the party of Mr Pena Nieto, the PRI.
